The state for each platform consists of the type and distance to the platform.

state = [type, distance]

	the type indicates if the platform is visible or not, or if it breaks (red platform)

	the distance is the vertical distance between the player and platform

get_state_num(n)
	returns the state for a particular platform n, with n in range [0,9]

get_states()
	returns an array of the states for all 10 platforms



brain.predict(state)
	returns the predicted reward of going to that platform

brain.reward(amount)
	rewards the previous prediction 

decide()
	is called by the game code and sets a global parameter target_platform

target_platform 
	is the current platform the doodle should try to get to

direction(n)
	tells the game which direction to move to get to the target_platform

